					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=213153&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182737" alt="DrClef" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=213153)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;" >DrClef</a></span> <span class="odate time_1389557657 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Jan 2014 20:14</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1934284">
									

<p>I like -morph, but clarified its meaning. Also clarified the meaning of Freud-class, as the one I had was too broad. Also loving &quot;Ebbinghaus.&quot;</p>
<p>I changed a few of the other codewords.</p>
<p>1. Naga seemed too passive for an organization as threatening to the GOC as the Hand, so I changed it to Hydra: cut off one head, two take its place.<br />
2. Roswell seemed too obvious. I changed it to &quot;Corona,&quot; the name of the county Roswell is located in.<br />
3. Salesmen became &quot;McConnell,&quot; the name of the founder of Avon Products.<br />
4. Merriment became Kringle. I hope you can guess why.</p>
<p>In general, I think a good rule of thumb to come up with codewords is to think of an obvious example of what you're using as your codeword, then choose a word related to it. This does mean that a few of the codewords are now too obvious, and may need to be changed (Plague for microorganism, for instance).</p>
<p>Thoughts?</p>

