<p>Now that this has been expanded a fair bit&#8230; I like it.</p>
<p>Few proposals for terms related to GOIs:</p>
<ul>
<li>perhaps a term for an artifact related to the SCP Foundation could be &quot;Gilligan&quot;? The anomalous world seems to like calling them Skippers, after all&#8230;</li>
<li>&quot;Perseus&quot; for ORIA. Alternatively, &quot;Andromeda&quot; or &quot;Cetus&quot;.</li>
<li>While not officially a group of interest, &quot;Morgenstern&quot; could be used for anything relating to Herman-Fuller's Circus of the Disquieting. (Anyone who gets that reference wins an internet.)</li>
<li>For the Fifth Church&#8230; I would say &quot;Hubbard&quot; but I would get sued. So, instead, &quot;Zealot&quot;, if that's not too on the nose.</li>
</ul>

